APIGateway:
    Functions as a singular point of entry for a microservice Architecture
    can perform load balancing at certain extent(Only for small applications)
    can implement security features like authentication/authorization but not limited to the same.
    also implements features like rate limiter.
    It routes the traffic to required services

Load Balancer:
    It's simple
    It's used there are alot of requests coming in.
    It routes request to necessary servers.
    It distributes requests as per utilization of servers
    It doesn't care much about what is the request.

Reverse Proxy:
    Forward Proxy funcitions as a recieptionist between user and internet
    Reverse Proxy functions as a recieptionist between internet and services
    Handles SSL/TSL, caching and hides backend servers
    Hides the addresses of backend services
